interactions.flavorLineOne: Zavala recognizes your devotion to completing Vanguard bounties and rewards you with a weapon worthy of that hard work.

"Enjoy the Games, Guardian. This is a chance for the people to see our passion for what we do." He lowers his voice. "And a chance for Titans to prove our mettle. Don't tell Ikora I said it, but the Warlocks are the ones to watch out for." He glances off toward the Bazaar. "Give them a fight they won't forget. Titans deserve a little time in the spotlight."

Zavala gazes toward the podium as you approach. "The Guardian Games were hard fought, but ultimately the Titans took the gold with shield and hammer." He's unable to hide the glint of pride in his eyes. "This is a victory for every Guardian. Titans may be on top right now, but the Warlocks and Hunters will work hard to make sure we don't stay there. That strengthens us all."

"Now if you'll excuse me, I need to prepare." The smile fades from Zavala's face. "Lord Shaxx is eager to celebrate our win in the 'traditional Titan way.'"

Zavala gazes toward the podium as you approach. "The Guardian Games were hard fought, but ultimately the Hunters took the gold with bow and blade." He shakes his head, unable to hide a small smile. "I may have been pulling for the Titans to bring us a victory, but when their backs are to the wall, count on Hunters to find a way every time."

"We all grow stronger together." Zavala adjusts his spaulders. "Next year my Titans will just have to grow a little more quickly."

Zavala gazes toward the podium as you approach. "The Guardian Games were hard fought, but ultimately the Warlocks took the gold with their finely honed powers." He glances down at his armor and rubs absently at a scuffed patch. "I would have preferred a Titan victory, but I can't say I'm surprised. Warlocks are true masters of the Light. They demand respect  and if it isn't given, they take it."

The ghost of a smile plays across Zavala's face. "Ikora taught me that. And I feel her Warlocks just taught their opponents the same lesson

"Welcome, Guardian," Zavala says as you approach. "My friend Eva Levante was kind enough to remind me that, even in times of crisis, people need levity and Light.

"And so I've proposed a new holiday: the Guardian Games. This is an opportunity for Titans, Warlocks, and Hunters to compete and demonstrate their unique strengths."

He hands you a piece of gear. "Wear this proudly. It will help you contribute to your class's score." He smiles. "And good luck, Guardian."

Zavala nods respectfully as you approach. His Ghost transmats a Grenade Launcher into his hands.

"This is the Wendigo, so-named for its monstrous hunger. Carry it with honor."

Zavala looks over the City. "Preparing for battle across four fronts we're spread too thin," he says quietly.

"As of now, our plan changes from preparation to evacuation."

He takes a measured breath. For a moment, he looks old.

"Sloane asked whether we could spare a Vanguard ship to relocate important cargo. Coming from her, that's a full-on distress call. Head to Titan, help her tie up loose ends, and bring her home."

"I have also been in contact with Asher Mir on Io. He insists the data he's gathering is too important to abandon. Of course, his phrasing was a bit more colorful."

You nod.

"Thank you, Guardian," he says reflexively. It's clear his mind is far away.

"The Pyramids are on our doorstep," Zavala says as you arrive. "Eris is researching the signals. Even the Drifter is helping, in his way."

There's no hesitation in his voice as the commander gives his orders.

"Eris made Io her base of operations, but she can't report on the surface while she's studying that tree. Meet up with Asher Mir. He should have some strong opinions about what to do next."

"Down on Titan, Sloane should be more pragmatic. She'll want to tear the ship from the sky with her bare hands."

You see a glint in his eyes. "See that she does."

Never a dull moment for the Vanguard. While Zavala orchestrates regular operations across the system and directs the fight to keep our hold on the Moon, he trusts you and Ikora to tackle the Vex crisis head-on.

headerDisplayProperties.description: Speak with Zavala about the emerging Vex crisis on the Moon.
headerDisplayProperties.name: The Vex Offensive

interactions.flavorLineOne:
"The Festival of the Lost is a City-wide tradition," Zavala says. "Guardians see death differently than others do, but we all know loss. And that brings us together."

He smiles. "As does celebration. We remember the dead and celebrate the living, so enjoy yourself, Guardian."

Zavala is amazed by your continuing ability to do the impossible. On behalf of the City, he thanks you for saving Saint-14. He also asks that you help Saint-14 adjust to his new life in the Tower however you can. He expects his return to the City will be a little overwhelming.

headerDisplayProperties.description: Commander Zavala has heard of your success in saving Saint-14 from the Infinite Forest and wishes to thank you. Visit him in the Tower Courtyard.
headerDisplayProperties.name: Zavala

interactions.flavorLineOne:
"When you achieve the success seen here today, it's not just a personal victory. It's a victory for us all. You ensure that the enemy knows we give no quarter."

Zavala offers a small nod of approval. "Take this and keep reminding them."

"Shock tactics are an important tool for the Vanguard," Zavala says. "The aural and optical devastation of a large ordnance provides a significant tactical advantage and wreaks havoc on enemy morale. Further, while I'm glad to have the comms channels free of such bombast"

A hint of a smile flashes across his face.

"even I'll admit the experience is satisfying. Take this, Guardian, and make sure they get your message."

No need to waver, Guardian. The Vanguard stands behind you every step of the way.

The Light is our strength. The Darkness will never take that from us. 

Fight on.

"Welcome to the Tower, Guardian. I am Commander Zavala. I, and every citizen of the Last City, need your help."

Commander Zavala is the leader of the Vanguard. He offers bounties, quests, and special rewards for challenges in strike activities.

Hover over the quest icon below and select it with .


ACQUIRE QUEST

The City has been liberated, but threats to our survival remain. Zavala has authorized the Nightfall protocol to dispatch elite Guardian fireteams for surgical strikes against the greatest of these threats. 

Each week, assemble your fireteam and complete the Nightfall strike to earn valuable rewards.
Zavala congratulates you on your performance in strikesand offers a reward fit for such a heroic effort.
Zavala thanks you for the thoughtful gift, and begins squeezing it immediately. Forcefully.

With a quiet kind of ceremony, Zavala presents you with your reward: a new Oxygen SR3.

"Carry it proudly," he tells you.
Zavala congratulates you on your dedication to fighting the biggest threats to humanity, and he gives you a reward worthy of your heroism.
Zavala's expression is unreadable as he accepts the cookies, but he nods in recognition of the thoughtful gift.

Zavala nods approvingly as you approach.

"Excellent work, Guardian. Even smaller tasks play a big part in the Vanguard's operations. Your diligence sets a strong example for us all."

"Welcome back, Guardian. Your fight against the enemies at our gates has only just begun."

Return to Commander Zavala to acquire bounties, gear, and other rewards related to strike activities.

Zavala carries upon his shoulders the burden of guilt for the loss of the City. The truth is this was a wake-up call for all of humanity. It's time to shore up our defenses and take the fight to our enemies. 

Report back to Zavala for Nightfall and strike activities.

Zavala will never trust Rasputin, but for now he'll put his faith in Ana Bray. The future may be uncertain, but he is reassured knowing he has a Guardian he can trust. You have earned his praise by destroying Xol and saving Mars.
Zavala doesn't have the luxury of revenge. He has the City to think of. He won't give you his blessing as you head to the Tangled Shore in mission "High Plains Blues."
You got the revenge you wanted, but Commander Zavala reminds you of what you risked to do so. Uldren's death will have consequences. Of that Zavala is sure.

"You have stood against every foe and driven them to break. A commendable effort, Guardian. One that does not go unnoticed.

"I assume you've heard the people recounting your deeds throughout the City? You command their respect, and hold their hope. They look to you as the first who will stand against the coming tide. I know you will not fail them. Carry on." Commander Zavala

"Guardian To hold off oblivion, we must be vigilant against the enemies who threaten our existence."

Vanguard bounties offer focused objectives for Guardians to complete while playing strike activities.

Select Vanguard bounties from Commander Zavala. Complete their objectives, then claim your completed bounties to gain XP and rewards.

You bring your collected reports to Zavala. He looks them over slowly, one entry at a time.

"Give Sloane the time she needs to come up with her plan," he says. "She's the best there is."

"Asher, on the other hand his theories had better produce resultsand quickly."

"Ana thinks some part of Rasputin survived? I hope she's right, for all our sakes."

"Vance's reaction is troubling. We need him clearheaded. Fanaticism is a luxury we cannot afford."

"Our territories are holding together," Zavala says, but the tension doesn't leave his face. "Continue to aid them in any way you can."

"Thank you," he says, and turns back to the Traveler.

Commander Zavala straightens his stance and meets your eyes directly. "I've heard of your adventures." His shoulders relax. "Impeccable work, Guardian. You've transcended our expectations yet again."

Zavala buries a prideful smile. "However, there is always more work to be done. Remain on the fireteam, and remain vigilant. Carry on."

"How are the evacuations proceeding?"

The commander doesn't wait for an answer, as though he already knows. He speaks with single-minded purpose.

"On Mars, Ana Bray believes she can salvage part of Rasputin. I hope she's right. Help her, then get her off-world safely."

"I've also received strange messages from Vance about being drawn to the Infinite Forest. This isn't the time for a pilgrimage. Bring him back to the Tower."

"Help them understandhelp them all understand," Zavala says and sets his jaw. "We don't leave people behind."

"The Darkness is pushing deeper into our territory," Zavala intones gravely. The air around him crackles with energy.

"Mars. Tell Ana Bray what we've learned about the Pyramids so far. Help her defend against the creatures they draw."

"Then I need you on Mercury. Vance is in the Lighthouse there and needs to be brought up to speed. The Infinite Forest has strategic value but is not our top priority."

The air is suddenly still. Zavala speaks softly, almost to himself.

"There's so much we can't afford to lose."
Without another word, Zavala hands you a weapon.

Zavala looks over the City. "Preparing for battle across four fronts we're spread too thin," he says quietly.

"As of now, our plan changes from preparation to evacuation."

He takes a measured breath. For a moment, he looks old.

"Sloane asked whether we could spare a Vanguard ship to relocate important cargo. Coming from her, that's a full-on distress call. Head to Titan, help her tie up loose ends, and bring her home."

"I have also been in contact with Asher Mir on Io. He insists the data he's gathering is too important to abandon. Of course, his phrasing was a bit more colorful."

You nod.

"Thank you, Guardian," he says reflexively. It's clear his mind is far away.
Your reputation in the Crucible precedes you. Take this reward in recognition of your deeds.
